# def to load dat
def load_dat(basis, model, which_feature):
    '''load all the stat files for a certain feature from all ds.
    '''
    indir = './perprog_{0}/{1}_stat.npy'.format(basis, model)
    return numpy.load(indir).tolist()[which_feature]

# def for get energy
def load_energy(basis, ):
    
    dat_in = open('../../6.data.prepare/2.ener.get/path_ener.{0}.dat'.format(basis), 'r')

    # initialize parameters
    pathway = []

    line = dat_in.readline()
    pathway = []
    while line:
    
        if line == '===begin===\n':
            state = dat_in.readline().split().pop()
            pathid = dat_in.readline().split().pop()       # pathid line read
        elif line == '===+end+===\n':
            pass
        else:
            words = line.split()
            pathway.append(float(words[1]),)
        line = dat_in.readline()
    return pathway

def load_progress(basis):
    '''load 1d tsne data.
    numpy.array of shape (900, )
    '''
    indir = './aligned_prog_{0}.npy'.format(basis)
    return numpy.load(indir).reshape(900,).tolist()

bss_index=3
model_list = ['svr', 'gpr', 'krr', ]
feature_labels = ['P0', 'P1', 'P2', 'P3', 'B0', 'B1', 'H0', 'H1', 'H2', ]

r02highylim=0.175 if bss_index==0 else 0.125
r3lowylim=-40 if bss_index==0 else -30

for bss_index in range(0, 7):
    # colors & linestyle
    line_styles = ['-', '--', ':' ]
    mark_styles = ['o', '^', 's', 'x']
    colors = [(float(r/255), float(g/255), float(b/255), ) for r, g, b in [(230,  25,  75, ),
                                                                           ( 60, 180,  75, ), 
                                                                           (  0, 130, 200, ),
                                                                           (170, 110,  40, ),
                                                                           (240,  50, 230, ),
                                                                          ]
             ]

    # set up
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=4,
                             figsize=(7, 6), 
                             dpi=300, 
                             sharex=True, 
                             sharey='row',
                            )

    # ax general setup
    for r in range(4):
        ax=axes[r]

        # spine
        ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
        ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
        ax.spines['bottom'].set_linewidth(1.0)
        ax.spines['left'].set_linewidth(1.0)

        # tick & labels on x and y
        ax.tick_params(axis='y', which='major', direction='out',length=5, width=1)
        ax.tick_params(axis='y', which='minor', direction='out', length=3, width=1)
        ax.tick_params(axis='x', which='major', direction='out', length=5, width=1)
        ax.tick_params(axis='x', which='minor', direction='out', length=3, width=1)

            if fid in [2, 8, ]:

            if fid in [3 ]:

            errbar_higher = []

            for d in dat:
                x.append(d[0])
                aver_y.append(d[1])
                errbar_lower.append(d[3])
                errbar_higher.append(d[2])
                
            ax.plot(x,

                    c=c, 
                    ls=ls,

                    markersize=3 if fid != 3 else 5,

                    label=feature_labels[fid],

            if bss_index != 3:
                axes[0].legend(bbox_to_anchor=(0., 1.02, 1., .102), 
                           loc='lower left',
                           ncol=9, 
                           mode="expand",

                          )
                        
                
            errbar = [errbar_lower, errbar_higher]
            #ax.errorbar(x, aver_y, c=c, yerr=None, ls=ls, label = lbl, )

            # y=0 line
            ax.plot([-100, 100], [0, 0], c='grey', ls='-', lw=1)
        
            
        if bss_index != 3:
            if basis_list[bss_index] == 'sccdftb':

            elif basis_list[bss_index] == '6311++Gdp':

            text(0.02, 0.95, '{0} @ {1}'.format(model_list[r].upper(), basis_name ),

    ax=axes[3]

    # range
